# makepkg's build output. `packaging/local/` has had this file since it was
# created; `packaging/aur/` never did, so a `makepkg` run here left `src/` (the
# extracted release tarball - a whole second copy of the repo) and `pkg/` (the
# staged install tree, including two ~4MB compiled binaries) lying around, and
# a `git add`-everything commit swept all 505 files in.
#
# The root .gitignore does NOT cover this: its rules name `packages/**` - a
# different, real directory - not `packaging/**`.
#
# The release tarball + its signature are DOWNLOADS too: the PKGBUILD's
# `source=` fetches them from the GitHub release, so a copy here is makepkg's
# cache, not a source of truth. Keeping the 5.9MB tarball in git would also
# quietly pin the repo to one release forever.
src/
pkg/
*.pkg.tar.zst
*.tar.gz
*.tar.gz.sig
*.tar.gz.asc
*.log
